The paper focuses on developing security metrics for hosting providers in the fight against cybercrime, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper deals with issues related to data coverage and quality, normalization, aggregation, and metric interpretation, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cybercrime (cs.CY), social and information networks (cs.SI), software engineering (cs.SE), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
